# Amplify processes rules top-to-bottom and stops at the first match.
#
# 1. Let real files (hashed JS/CSS, images, prerendered */index.html, .xml, etc.)
#    win. Anything whose path contains a "." (a file extension) is served as-is,
#    so sitemap.xml, rss.xml, assets/*, og images, and per-route index.html files
#    are delivered literally instead of being rewritten to the SPA shell.
/<*>.<*>          /<*>.<*>          200

# 2. Prerendered route HTML: serve the route's OWN index.html, not the root one.
#    e.g. /blog/foo -> /blog/foo/index.html (written by scripts/prerender.js).
#    This is what makes prerendered per-route metadata reach crawlers/scrapers.
/<*>              /<*>/index.html  200

# 3. SPA fallback for anything still unmatched (e.g. /admin, /blueprint, an
#    un-prerendered deep client-only route) so React Router + NotFound still work.
/*                /index.html      200
